The paper discusses a novel system for targeting analogical search for specific design needs, which involves using machine learning and natural language processing techniques to identify relevant inspirations from distant domains. This suggests that the paper could belong to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) or Information Retrieval (cs.IR) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper focuses on human-computer interaction (HCI) and design, which suggests that it could also belong to the Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HC) sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of abstraction and optimization techniques, which suggests that it could belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) or Systems and Control (cs.SI) sub-categories.
